<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-937585" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/troops2.jpg?resize=300%2C213&#038;ssl=1" alt="Troops" width="300" height="213" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/troops2.jpg?resize=300%2C213&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/troops2.jpg?resize=58%2C41&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/troops2.jpg?resize=260%2C185&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/troops2.jpg?resize=183%2C130&amp;ssl=1 183w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/troops2.jpg?w=412&amp;ssl=1 412w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The arrest of the terrorists was made following an ongoing special military operation, tagged: “Operation Positive Identification “, by the Theatre Command of Operation Lafia Dole in the North East. Colonel Ado Isa, Deputy Director, Army Public Relations of Operation Lafiya Dole, in a statement, Monday morning, explained that Operation Positive Identification was launched across the three states of Adamawa, Yobe and Borno by the command “based on credible information that some of the fleeing criminals are hibernating in some towns and villages of Borno and Yobe States in particular and North East in general.” ALSO READ: Atiku: Boko Haram will be starved to death if we restructure To this end, the statement “enjoined members of the public to always carry valid means of identification such as National Identification Card when moving or passing through  Adamawa, Borno and Yobe States.” The statement read thus: “Following the commencement of “Operation positive Identification” by the Theatre Command Operation Lafiya Dole across the North-Eastern part of Nigeria, troops have intensified searching for and arresting all suspected criminal elements that roam parts of the North-Eastern part of Nigeria. “Consequently, 5 key terrorist logistics suppliers and fighters have so far been apprehended. “Recall that based on credible information that some of the fleeing criminals are hibernating in some towns and villages of Borno and Yobe states in particular and North East in general, the Theatre Command Operation Lafiya Dole enjoined members of the public to always carry valid means of identification such as National Identification Card when moving or passing through  Adamawa, Borno and Yobe States. “While troops are directed to strictly check legitimate means of identification such as National Identification Card, Voters Registration Card, Drivers’ License and International Passports or other valid official identification before allowing such person passage. “Consequently, Operation Positive Identification is seriously ongoing across the North East. “Members of the public are requested to cooperate with the troops by moving along with valid identification cards and present same to the troops in the efforts to rid the North-East zone of criminals fleeing for safety.” Vanguard  The Nigerian Army Theatre Command of Operation Lafiya Dole (OPLD) has urged Nigerian operating around the North East region of the country to carry valid identifications. September 22, 2019 In "News" The Nigerian Army Theatre Command of Operation Lafiya Dole (OPLD) has launched “Operation Positive Identification” against the fleeing Boko Haram/ISWAP terrorists in the North East. The Deputy Director, Army Public Relation, OPLD, Col. Ado Isa, disclosed this in a statement on Sunday. He urged the public to always carry valid… September 22, 2019 In "News" By: Kingsley Omonobi The Nigerian Army on Sunday 22 September arrested a gang of suspected cultists, who are suspected to engage in armed robbery and kidnapping in Maiduguri and its environs. Following credible information received from well-meaning individuals, the suspects were arrested, by troops of the Nigerian Army Super Cam